    public interface AttributeReadEnabled
    This interface gives read access to the enabled-flag of an object. Such object allows interactive behavior that can be enabled or disabled. If an object is disabled, the user can NOT interact with the object. This is typically visualized by greying out the object.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
    See Also:
    AttributeReadEditable, AttributeWriteEnabled

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isEnabled()
      This method determines if this object is enabled.

    • Method Detail

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        This method determines if this object is enabled. If it is NOT enabled, the user can NOT interact with the object.
        Returns:
        true if this object is enabled, false if this object is disabled.
